caption: Statue of 1896 Sculptor Jean Alexandre Joseph Falguière Pegasus carrying the poet towards the regions of dreams also known as Apollo on Pegasus. Pegasus is this fantastic winged horse from Greek mythology which symbolizes wisdom. He was born at the death of fear, which symbolized his mother Medusa... Wisdom overcoming fear. A muscular, robust Pegasus, only two hind legs support the entire sculpture, almost levitating. It really flies away! The poet is an adolescent, fine light the poet allegory of creation which points the finger upwards, they go towards Olympus... Wisdom.
Work by Alexandre Falguière dating from 1897. One of the only bronze statues that was not melted down during the Occupation.
Very beautiful sculpture at the bend of Place Edouard 7
in front of the Athénée theater
